Setting
  
“I have seen darkness so deep that it left scars in the form of nightmares that lasted years. I have also seen light so brilliant, so blinding that I still feel the warmth of it on my skin.”
        - Ellestriel, Queen of Summer

The world of Eld is a place of high fantasy. Bright light contrasts with deep darkness, where evil and depravity seek footholds in any place it can find. The shadow is not omnipresent, but the lights of civilization and justice are flames that need to be protected against the harsh winds.

A handful of months ago a Blood Moon appeared in the sky, bringing dark dreams and ominous portents. The shadows have grown longer, the nights have grown deeper, evil is moving, and the drums of war beat to someone’s tune…

